  "prompt": "What is the minimum marks needed to get mechanical branch in BITS Pilani?",
  "response": "The admission criteria for BITS Pilani, including the minimum marks required for the Mechanical Engineering branch, are primarily based on the BITS Admission Test (BITSAT) scores. The exact cutoff scores can vary each year based on factors like the number of applicants, overall performance, and the number of available seats.\n\nAs of my last update, the cutoff scores for different programs at BITS Pilani generally range between 290 and 350+ in BITSAT, with Mechanical Engineering traditionally being one of the more competitive branches. To get the most accurate and current information for a specific admission cycle, it's best to check the official BITS Pilani website or their admissions page, as they publish detailed information regarding cutoffs and other admission-related announcements every year.",
